How to use github
 Sign up & install Git
Create a GitHub account: Go to https://github.com and sign up.

Install Git: Download and install Git from https://git-scm.com.

üóÇÔ∏è Key Concepts
Term	Meaning
Repository (Repo)	A folder on GitHub where your project lives.
Commit	A snapshot of your changes.
Branch	A parallel line of development.
Merge	Combining branches together.
Pull Request (PR)	A request to merge changes into another branch.
Clone	Download a GitHub repo to your local machine.
Push	Upload your local commits to GitHub.
Pull	Download changes from GitHub to your machine.

üöÄ Common Workflows
2. Create a New Repository
On GitHub, click New repository.

Give it a name & description.

Choose public or private.

(Optional) Initialize with a README.

3. Clone a Repository
To work locally, run:

bash
Copy
Edit
git clone https://github.com/username/repo-name.git
cd repo-name
4. Make Changes
Edit files as needed. Then:

bash
Copy
Edit
git status      # See what changed
git add .       # Stage all changes
git commit -m "Describe your changes"
5. Push Changes to GitHub
bash
Copy
Edit
git push origin main
(Replace main with your branch name.)

6. Create a Branch
To safely develop new features:

bash
Copy
Edit
git checkout -b new-feature
After changes:

bash
Copy
Edit
git add .
git commit -m "Add new feature"
git push origin new-feature
7. Open a Pull Request
Go to your repo on GitHub.

Click Compare & pull request.

Add a description & reviewers.

Click Create pull request.

8. Merge & Delete Branch
After review, click Merge pull request.

Optionally delete the branch.

üîÑ Keeping Up To Date
If others pushed changes:

bash
Copy
Edit
git pull origin main
To update your feature branch:

bash
Copy
Edit
git checkout new-feature
git merge main
‚ú® Tips & Best Practices
‚úÖ Commit often with clear messages.
‚úÖ Use branches for features & fixes.
‚úÖ Pull before pushing to avoid conflicts.
‚úÖ Review code in pull requests before merging.

üìö Useful Git Commands Reference
Command	Description
git status	See current changes.
git log	View commit history.
git diff	See what‚Äôs changed.
git branch	List branches.
git checkout branch-name	Switch branches.
git merge branch-name	Merge into current branch.
git pull	Fetch & merge from remote.
git push	Upload changes to GitHub.

